  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;span&#xD;
    style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ES; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;&#xD;
     lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;>&lt;font face=&quot;Arial&quot;>To identify the services needed to perform the business processes modeled in the&#xD;
    Business Modeling Discipline, classifying them by type of service.&amp;nbsp;To define the Services Architecture diagram&#xD;
    specified in SoaML identifying participants, services to be provided to other parties and consumed from other parties&#xD;
    based on interchanged messages, and service contracts&amp;nbsp;to define the roles in the services&#xD;
    interaction.&lt;/font>&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
